SUMMARY:Yoga Vinyasa Krama 
DESCRIPTION:Nataraja School of Traditional Yoga\n**Yoga Vinyasa Krama - Th
 ursdays 9-10:30am**\n**Songbird Community Healing Center Cotati**\n\nExper
 ience physical health & fitness\, pranic flow\, vital energy & stillness -
  through intelligent architecture with the metaphysics of deep conscious b
 reathing & slow motion\, yogic breathwork\, mantra/sound/vibration\, mudra
 \, subtle & contemplative practices.\n\nYoga Vinyasa Krama is a comprehens
 ive hatha-raja yogic system for purification\, developing concentration\, 
 neuromuscular fitness and conditioning\, mastering the breath\, awakening 
 subtle energy and stilling the mind. Based on deep breathing & the subtle 
 movement of prana directed into the cartilage tissue\, sinuous musculature
 \, internal organs\, nerve pathways and nadis. It has over 700 intelligent
 ly sequenced slow\, conscious breath powered with precision movement varia
 tions with pause (vinyasas)\, exploring many aesthetic variations of each 
 posture to correctly establish the main asanas while the mind merges with 
 the breath.\nIncludes drishti\, pratikriyas\, bandha\, vaseth\, mudra\, ma
 ntra\, surya & ding namaskar with breath & mantra\, cleansing kriyas\, Him
 alayan pranayama including including ujjayi variations\, heating & cooling
  breaths\, solar\, lunar & soli-lunar nadi shuddhi practices\, pranava & s
 amantraka pranayama\, pratyahara\, subtle & contemplative practices in 12 
 kramas (sequences).\n\nThe whole process gradually transforms the body and
  mind\, releasing old patterns of physical and mental tension and dysfunct
 ional patterns of movement\, providing tonic\, energetic and psychophysiol
 ogical effects. This system is presented from the teachings Srivatsa Ramas
 wami learned through his over 33 years of one on one study with Sri Krishn
 amacharya and teachings from a similar Himalayan method.\n\nThis ongoing c
 lass will explore the entire system of 12 Kramas with each class focusing 
 on a particular krama (sequence) & pranayama & contemplative practices.\n\
 nPlease practice on an empty stomach. Morning beverage ok but please take 
 it 30min or more before class.\n\n*Certain injuries & health issues may be
  contraindicated Please contact me if you have a concern*\nKnowledge of Co
 rrect Ujjayi Breathing recommended\n**$25 Drop In\, Discounted Class Passe
 s\, Sliding Scale Available**\n**RSVP Only Contact Kara @707-235-1413\, su
 nyogadance@gmail.com**
